.:: Puzzle 4x3-Level-2-17::.
3 different brands of cigars are smoked: cain, swisher, fonseca
City: rome, san-francisco, edinburgh
The people's birthday is in 3 different months: june, april, may
The people use 3 different means of transport: airplane, ship, train
1. the person traveling to san-francisco is between the person driving the train and the person traveling to rome##2
2. the person who's birthday is in may is on the right of the person driving the train##1
3. the swisher-smoker is the person who's birthday is in june##1
4. the person who's birthday is in may is the cain-smoker##1
5. the person driving the airplane is the person who's birthday is in april##1
6. the person traveling to rome is on the right of the person driving the ship##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |   2    |    3     |
| Cigar   | swisher | cain  | fonseca     |
| City   | edinburgh    | san-francisco | rome |
| Birthday           | june        | may   | april  |
| Transport     | train      | ship   | airplane |

